article.description: Long Island U. 85, St. Francis, Pa. 71
article.headline: Long Island U. 85, St. Francis, Pa. 71
article.linkText: Long Island U. 85, St. Francis, Pa. 71
article.story: NEW YORK -- Jaytornah Wisseh led six double-figure scorers with 19 points to lead Long Island University to an 85-71 win over St. Francis Pa. on Thursday night. Lucas Faggiano added 13 points for the Blackbirds (14-12, 10-5 Northeast). LIU had won 3 straight. Junior Devin Sweetney had a career-high 35 points for the Red Flash (5-21, 2-13), who lost their sixth straight. After Kurt Hoffman got the visitors within 26-20 with 7:35 left in the half, the Blackbirds went on a 15-2 run for a 41-22 lead. Julian Boyd had seven in the run. LIU shot 57 percent for the game.
